title: Sources: Kelly leaving Ohio St. to be Raiders' OC
description: Chip Kelly is returning to the NFL to become the Las Vegas Raiders' offensive coordinator under new head coach Pete Carroll, sources told ESPN's Adam Schefter and Pete Thamel.
author: Paul Gutierrez

title: AD pivotal to Mavs' 'vision,' 'culture,' GM says
description: Dallas Mavericks general manager Nico Harrison, sitting alongside coach Jason Kidd on Sunday, emphasized the importance of "culture" in explaining his stunning decision to trade Luka Doncic to the Los Angeles Lakers for a package headed by Anthony Davis.
author: Tim MacMahon

title: 'Who are you?' Everyone knows who Lewis-Skelly is now
description: Five months ago, Erling Haaland responded to Arsenal teenager Myles Lewis-Skelly's attempt to confront him with a dismissive: "Who are you?" The Man City striker knows now, writes Phil McNulty.

title: 'I just want to play football' - Rashford joins Villa on loan
description: Aston Villa complete the loan signing of Manchester United forward Marcus Rashford.

title: Liverpool look unstoppable as Hurzeler shows his inexperience
Azim hammers former champion Lipinets to seize stoppage victory
description: Adam Azim scored a dominant victory over Sergey Lipinets to win their Wembley Arena clash inside nine rounds.

title: The big question around the Luka Dončić trade: Why did Dallas do it?
description: A young talent who never would have been moved in the past gets a new home with the Lakers (of course), and it raises a number of questions for the future.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Lions QB Jared Goff wins Pro Bowl Games offensive MVP honors in NFC's 76-63 win over AFC
description: AFC head coach Peyton Manning had jokes for the light-hearted affair, which he has lost three straight years against his younger brother Eli.
